bug.short_desc: Panning and opening the side panel can occasionally leave a graphic defect

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 524074 screenshot
Mozilla/5.0 (Android; Linux armv71; rv2.2a1pre) Gecko/20110405 Firefox/4.2a1pre Fennec/4.1a1pre Device: Droid 2 OS: Android 2.2
1. go to about:firstrun 2. pan down and open the tab side panel in one motion
Expected: no graphic defect Actual: occasionally you may get a graphic defect
Sounds like a bug Chris Jones fixed a month ago or so except that there is no highlight here (bug 637822)
